4)append

temp = [1.2,3.4,5.6]
temp.append(10.10)
o/p=> [1.2,3.4,5.6,10.10]

4.1) clear

temp.clear()

o/p =>[]

4.3) index

temp.index(3.4)

o/p=> 1 

5)Accessing item from list

temp = [1.2,3.4,5.6]

temp._getitem_(1)

o/p => 3.4

we can also use [] insted of_getitem_()

temp[1]
==> 3.4

6)Accessing list slices

temp =[1.2,3.4,5.6,10.10,11.11]

temp[1:4]

=o/p ===> [3.4,5.6,10.10,11.11] ==>it will return list of item from 1 to 4

temp[0:2] or temp[:2]
o/p=>>[1.2,3.4,5.6]

temp[3:4] or temp[3:]

o/p ==> [10.10,11.11]

7) negetive value 

temp[-1] ==> 11.11

temp[-2] ==>10.10

temp[-3] ==>5.6

we can also use slicing with negetive value :

temp[-2:] ===>[10.10,11.11]

8) Accessing characters and slice in string :

mystring = 'hello'

mystring[1] ===> e

mystring[-1] => l

mystring[:3] ===> hel


we can also have list of diffrent data types like

temp = ['hello', 1, 2 3]

temp[0]====> hello

temp[0][2] ===>l


